text.__SUMMARY__: Trimeresurus insularis is a venomous pit viper subspecies found in Indonesia and East Timor. Common names include: white-lipped island pit viper, Lesser Sunda pit viper, and Sunda Island pit viper.
text.Description: The scalation includes 21 rows of dorsal scales at midbody, 156-164/156-167 ventral scales in males/females, 70-75/54-59 subcaudal scales in males/females, and 7-12 supralabial scales.
text.Geographic range: Found in Indonesia on eastern Java, Bali, Lombok, Sumbawa, Sumba, Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Adonara, Lembata, Pantar, Alor, Roti, Semau, Timor, Wetar, Kisar and Romang. The type locality given is "Soe, Timor".
